        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43673",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've attached a patch which includes the suggested modification, plus four test cases to reproduce the issue.\r\nPHPUnit testdox output:\r\n [x] Should not return port when scheme is http and port is 80\r\n [x] Should not return port when scheme is https and port is 443\r\n [x] Should return port when scheme is http and port is not 80\r\n [x] Should return port when scheme is https and port is not 443\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-17T11:43:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-17T11:44:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43765",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Some other components do appear to rely on this behavior, such as Zend_Oauth:\r\n{code}\r\n1) Zend_OauthTest::testGetHttpClientResetsParameters\r\nFailed asserting that two strings are equal.\r\n--- Expected\r\n+++ Actual\r\n@@ @@\r\n-http:\/\/www.example.com:80\r\n+http:\/\/www.example.com\r\n{code}\r\nUnfortunately, the change you've requested will most likely cause a bc break, and so will not be accepted in 1.x.  I think this should be pushed up to 2.x for fixing (if the issue also exists there). \r\n\r\nIt may be a simple matter of correcting the tests, but I would like someone with more experience with this component (Zend_Uri) to comment on that. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-19T19:24:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-20T05:43:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43766",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=patrickg",
                        "name": "patrickg",
                        "displayName": "Patrick G\u00fcnther",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Okay. Here's my workaround for people who want to avoid this problem.\r\n\r\n{code}if (('http' == $uri->getScheme() && 80 == $uri->getPort()) ||\r\n    ('https' == $uri->getScheme() && 443 == $uri->getPort())\r\n) {\r\n    $uri->setPort('');\r\n}{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=patrickg",
                        "name": "patrickg",
                        "displayName": "Patrick G\u00fcnther",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-19T22:23:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-19T22:23:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46071",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Could a member of the Zend Framework development team comment on this issue? Would changing this behavior be considered a BC break?  After applying my patch, Zend_OauthTest::testGetHttpClientResetsParameters fails as it relies on the \"broken\" behavior (see my earlier comment above).  The test in question specifically tests for that case:\r\n\r\n{code:}\r\npublic function testGetHttpClientResetsParameters()\r\n{\r\n    $client = new Test_Http_Client_19485876();\r\n    $client->setParameterGet(array('key'=>'value'));\r\n    Zend_Oauth::setHttpClient($client);\r\n    $resetClient = Zend_Oauth::getHttpClient();\r\n    $resetClient->setUri('http:\/\/www.example.com');\r\n    $this->assertEquals('http:\/\/www.example.com:80', $resetClient->getUri(true));\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nNotice that it calls setUri('http:\/\/www.example.com') but asserts for http:\/\/www.example.com:80\r\n\r\nThanks!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-04-28T12:04:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-04-28T12:05:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46074",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nThe fact that this breaks some tests is good, because this is a BC breakage and I would not introduce such a change until ZF 2.0 unless there is a good reason to do so. This bug is marked as \"Minor\" and I do not see any reason stated why this is causing real problems - I agree it's not pretty but is it really causing issues?\r\n\r\nThis issue is already addresses in the design of Zend\\Uri for 2.0 - If you want you are welcome to take a peek at the proposal (it actually points to a partial implementation you can checkout using git) at http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFPROP\/Zend_Uri+2.0+-+Shahar+Evron\r\n\r\nIf you think there is a reason for BC breakage before 2.0, please elaborate. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-04-28T13:10:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-04-28T13:10:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46174",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Shahar, \r\n\r\nI completely agree.  It is more of an annoyance than an issue, and I can't think of any meaningful cases where having the default port number specified for http\/https would cause an issue, as it is still a valid URI.  I've closed the issue, as you point out that it's been fixed in ZF2's Zend\\Uri.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-04-28T21:40:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-04-28T21:40:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46175",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Change would cause BC break.  Issue has been resolved in ZF2 Zend\\Uri",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-04-28T21:41:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-04-28T21:41:08.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
